First Take on TS in nodeJS and express
-pedrotech

--- super basic


1. install ts globally
  terminal => npm i -g typescript
  check => tsc --version / tsc -v
  
  
2. open new empty project.
3. initialize TS => tsc --init ==> will create a tsconfig json file


basic config -
uncomment:

rootDir: --- ts files to be compiled into JS
outDir: --- create folder where you want your compiled ts into js will be stored
moduleResolution: "node" 


--install packages needed for basic epxress ts project

npm i express  


-install types needed as dev dependencies

npm i --save-dev @types/express @types/node typescript nodemon ts-node



